OpenVPN Cookbook Chapter 6 sample code

The samples in this chapter are openvpn configuration files, 
as well as some helper scripts.

Chapter 6 is divided up into 10 recipes. Below is a list of which
configuration file is used in which recipe.

6.1 Using a Client-side up/down script
server: example6-1-server.conf
client: example6-1.ovpn
script: updown.bat

6.2 Windows login greeter
server: example6-2-server.conf
client: example6-2.ovpn
script: example6-2.vbs

6.3 Using client-connect /client-disconnect scripts
server: example6-3-server.conf
client: example6-3.ovpn
scripts: example6-3-connect.sh, example6-3.vbs

6.4 Using a 'learn-address' script
server: example6-4-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.ovpn
script: example6-4-learn-address.sh

6.5 Using a 'tls-verify' script
server: example6-5-server.conf
client: basic-udp-client.ovpn
scripts: example6-5-tls-verify.sh, example6-5-tls-verify.sh.allowed

6.6 Using a 'auth-user-pass-verify' script
server: example6-6-server.conf
client: example6-6-client.conf
scripts: example6-6-aupv.sh, example6-6-aupv.sh.passwd

6.7 Script order
server: example6-7-server.conf
client: example6-6-client.conf
script: example6-7-script.sh

6.8 Script security and logging
server: example6-1-server.conf
client: example6-8-client.conf
script: example6-8-up.sh

6.9 Using the 'down-root' plugin
server: example6-9-server.conf
script: example6-9.sh

6.10 Using the PAM authentication plugin
server: example6-10-server.conf
client: example6-10.ovpn
